  "cooked": "<p>While trying to illustrate the griefing attack with a functional test, I found another bug <img src=\"https://delvingbitcoin.org/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> Will link to a fix PR here.</p>\n<p>Update:</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox githubpullrequest\" data-onebox-src=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/31600\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/31600\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"github-row\" data-github-private-repo=\"false\">\n\n\n\n    <div class=\"github-icon-container\" title=\"Pull Request\">\n      <svg width=\"60\" height=\"60\" class=\"github-icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 12 16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11 11.28V5c-.03-.78-.34-1.47-.94-2.06C9.46 2.35 8.78 2.03 8 2H7V0L4 3l3 3V4h1c.27.02.48.11.69.31.21.2.3.42.31.69v6.28A1.993 1.993 0 0 0 10 15a1.993 1.993 0 0 0 1-3.72zm-1 2.92c-.66 0-1.2-.55-1.2-1.2 0-.65.55-1.2 1.2-1.2.65 0 1.2.55 1.2 1.2 0 .65-.55 1.2-1.2 1.2zM4 3c0-1.11-.89-2-2-2a1.993 1.993 0 0 0-1 3.72v6.56A1.993 1.993 0 0 0 2 15a1.993 1.993 0 0 0 1-3.72V4.72c.59-.34 1-.98 1-1.72zm-.8 10c0 .66-.55 1.2-1.2 1.2-.65 0-1.2-.55-1.2-1.2 0-.65.55-1.2 1.2-1.2.65 0 1.2.55 1.2 1.2zM2 4.2C1.34 4.2.8 3.65.8 3c0-.65.55-1.2 1.2-1.2.65 0 1.2.55 1.2 1.2 0 .65-.55 1.2-1.2 1.2z\"></path></svg>\n    </div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-info-container\">\n\n\n\n      <h4>\n        <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/31600\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">rpc: fix mintime field testnet4, expand timewarp attack test</a>\n      </h4>\n\n    <div class=\"branches\">\n      <code>bitcoin:master</code> \u2190 <code>Sjors:2025/01/timewarp-oops</code>\n    </div>\n\n      <div class=\"github-info\">\n        <div class=\"date\">\n          opened <span class=\"discourse-local-date\" data-format=\"ll\" data-date=\"2025-01-03\" data-time=\"14:41:39\" data-timezone=\"UTC\">02:41PM - 03 Jan 25 UTC</span>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"user\">\n          <a href=\"https://github.com/Sjors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n            <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://delvingbitcoin.org/uploads/default/original/1X/37e9679d22884392534900d6028f1cc537512e9b.png\" class=\"onebox-avatar-inline\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" data-dominant-color=\"6C6963\">\n            Sjors\n          </a>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"lines\" title=\"3 commits changed 4 files with 44 additions and 17 deletions\">\n          <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/31600/files\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n            <span class=\"added\">+44</span>\n            <span class=\"removed\">-17</span>\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-row\">\n    <p class=\"github-body-container\">#30681 fixed the `curtime` field of `getblocktemplate` to take the timewarp rule<span class=\"show-more-container\"><a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/31600\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"show-more\">\u2026</a></span><span class=\"excerpt hidden\"> into account. However I forgot to do the same for the `mintime` field, which was hardcoded to use `pindexPrev-&gt;GetMedianTimePast()+1`.\n\nThis PR adds a helper `GetMinimumTime()` and uses it for the `mintime` field.\n\nIt could be backported to v28. However I don't expect (testnet4) pools to use `mintime` in practice, since under normal mainnet circumstances this would produce blocks an hour in the past.\n\n\nAdditionally this PR adjusts the timewarp test to better illustrate the griefing attack discussed here: https://delvingbitcoin.org/t/timewarp-attack-600-second-grace-period/1326/19 \n\nChanging `MAX_TIMEWARP` to something `&gt; MAX_FUTURE_BLOCK_TIME` in `consensus.h` and `mining_basic.py` will cause the updated test to fail. I'm not proposing such a change here of course. The new test should be useful guidance for pool software developers, for why they really should use `curtime`, or least not ignore `mintime`.</span></p>\n  </div>\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>Aside from the fix it illustrates the griefing attack above.</p>",
